French President
Emmanuel Macron noted on Saturday that all sides in the conflict in the Democratic
Republic of Congo had agreed to support a ceasefire.  During talks with
Angolan President Joao Lourenco and DRC President Felix Tshisekedi, as well as
Rwandan President Paul Kagame, Macron said all had "given clear
support" to a ceasefire next Tuesday, as envisaged in the timeline
mediated by Angola.